{
  "texts": [
    "To reduce this cost, we exploit the union mask D = M ({y w, y l }), and create a jointly masked input y \\D, where all differing positions between y w and y l are masked.",
    "One forward pass on y \\D provides logits for all positions.",
    "We then approximate log p(y w) ≈ i∈D log p(y wi |y \\D) (same for y l).",
    "Positions outside D do not need to be evaluated since their logits agree.",
    "This is equivalent to a mean-field approximation, where we assume that, conditional on the observed tokens, the masked positions are independent."
  ]
}